sql:
SELECT AVG(growth_rate) AS average_growth_rate
FROM population_growth_rates
WHERE country_id IN (
    SELECT country_id 
    FROM life_expectancy 
    WHERE female_life_expectancy > (
        SELECT AVG(female_life_expectancy) 
        FROM life_expectancy
    )
);

SELECT country_name
  FROM countries
  WHERE country_id IN (
    SELECT country_id
    FROM population_growth_rates
    WHERE growth_rate < (
      SELECT AVG(growth_rate)
      FROM population_growth_rates
    )
  );

external_knowledge:
"More recent year that was analyzed" refers to the year 2022;
The demographic details involve population count, growth rates, and life expectancy trends;
Ordering is based on the alphabetical order of country names.

- "Teeming with life and vitality" represents high fertility rates, long life expectancies for both males and females, and a notable gender ratio;
- "Waves of births are frequent" refers to high fertility rates;
- "Scales of gender balance" metaphorically represents the ratio of males to females;
- "Ocean of more than 10 million" means the population exceeds 10,000,000.

